<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12138l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12138l">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12138l"> 138(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lunar calendar (flood)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In Egypt, with the annual flood of the Nile, it must have been difficult for the agriculturalist, without some method of counting time, to know exactly when to begin operations.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The Egyptians used, in the first instance, <mark>the lunar calendar</mark> in order to calculate this important date. <small> William James Perry, <a name="ORMR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ORMR"><cite title="source">Origin of Magic and Religion</cite></a> (1923) 30-1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
